                            <comment id="14455927" author="kutzi@gmx.de" created="Fri, 5 Jul 2013 05:23:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Test project to reproduce the issue&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455863" author="agudian" created="Tue, 9 Jul 2013 17:15:18 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for the report and the sample! &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Fixed with commit 50912ac6f0dae8d9dec0a7c7638f24addc7336b7, extended the integration tests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Please give 2.16-SNAPSHOT a spin as soon as the artefacts are promoted (give it at least 5 hours).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455840" author="agudian" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 07:06:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;FYI, it still doesn&apos;t work for TestNG 5.14 - all other tested versions work (including 5.14.1 and the latest 6.8.5). So I don&apos;t care about 5.14.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14457013" author="kutzi@gmx.de" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 07:11:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for fixing this!&lt;br/&gt;
It&apos;s now at lot more than 5 hours later and still I cannot fetch 2.16-SNAPSHOT from central.&lt;br/&gt;
Any ETA when it will be there?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455996" author="agudian" created="Wed, 10 Jul 2013 07:33:47 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;You have to add the apache snapshot repository as pluginRepository. The artefacts are already there:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://repository.apache.org/content/groups/snapshots&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://repository.apache.org/content/groups/snapshots&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14457007" author="kutzi@gmx.de" created="Fri, 12 Jul 2013 09:54:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks much better now - at least the settings do seem to have some effect.&lt;br/&gt;
However, the ordering doesn&apos;t seem to be globally - e.g. when I use alphabetical it runs &apos;some&apos; tests ordered A-Z, but then after Z, again some other A tests come (I have to come up with an isolated test case for that)&lt;br/&gt;
Is the ordering somehow scoped to package o.s.l.t.?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, is ordering meant to be on class level, method level or both? The documentation doesn&apos;t say anything about that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14455890" author="kutzi@gmx.de" created="Fri, 12 Jul 2013 10:00:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Also: when I run a specific test class (via mvn -Dtest=ATestClass test), then runOrder still doesn&apos;t seem to be applied. Is this by design?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456013" author="agudian" created="Fri, 12 Jul 2013 10:39:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;AFAIK, the runOrder applies on class level only. I&apos;d have to check if it is passed to JUnit in some special way to also affect the method level there, but I doubt it. Everything within the classes or the user defined suites is something the test framework has to deal with.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14456036" author="agudian" created="Sat, 13 Jul 2013 13:59:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;OK, checked again, and I had it remembered right: runOrder works on class level. When using alphabetical or reversealphabetical, the fully qualified class name is used in the comparison.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anything left that you feel is wrong?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14457010" author="kutzi@gmx.de" created="Mon, 15 Jul 2013 03:44:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Okay, I didn&apos;t realise that ordering could be by &apos;fully qualified&apos; class name. That probably explains, what I had seen.&lt;br/&gt;
So, there&apos;s currently nothing left, which I feel could be wrong.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17994411" author="olamy" created="Fri, 4 Jul 2025 07:21:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This project has moved from Jira to GitHub Issues. This issue was migrated to &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/maven-surefire/issues/1558&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;apache/maven-surefire#1558&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
